SIMPLE: migratory
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Migratory
<hw>Mi"gra*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>migratoire</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Removing regularly or occasionally from one region
or climate to another; <as>as, <ex>migratory</ex> birds</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, roving; wandering; nomad; <as>as,
<ex>migratory</ex> habits; a <ex>migratory</ex> life.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Migratory locust</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>See
<er>Locust</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Migratory thrush</b></col>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the American robin. See
<er>Robin</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mikado</ent>⟦br⟧
